### Obtener todos los clientes
GET http://localhost:8081/api/v2/clientes
Accept: application/json

###

### Obtener cliente por ID
GET http://localhost:8081/api/v2/clientes/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Obtener cliente por RUT
GET http://localhost:8081/api/v2/clientes/rut/12345678-9
Accept: application/json

###

### Crear nuevo cliente
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v2/clientes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rut": "12345678-9",
  "nombre": "Juan",
  "apellido": "Pérez",
  "email": "juan.perez@email.com",
  "telefono": "+56912345678"
}

###

### Actualizar cliente
PUT http://localhost:8081/api/v2/clientes/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rut": "12345678-9",
  "nombre": "Juan",
  "apellido": "González",
  "email": "juan.gonzalez@email.com",
  "telefono": "+56987654321"
}

###

### Eliminar cliente
DELETE http://localhost:8081/api/v2/clientes/1

###

### Crear cliente con RUT duplicado (debe retornar 400)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v2/clientes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rut": "12345678-9",
  "nombre": "Pedro",
  "apellido": "López",
  "email": "pedro.lopez@email.com",
  "telefono": "+56911111111"
}

###

### Actualizar cliente inexistente (debe retornar 404)
PUT http://localhost:8081/api/v2/clientes/9999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rut": "99999999-9",
  "nombre": "Inexistente",
  "apellido": "Inexistente",
  "email": "no@existe.com",
  "telefono": "+56900000000"
}

###

### Eliminar cliente inexistente (debe retornar 404)
DELETE http://localhost:8081/api/v2/clientes/9999
